State of Open Campus Q2 2025

Austin Freimuth

3 days ago   12 min read

Key Insights

  • EDUs token price rose 15.8% QoQ to $0.13 and its circulating market capitalization increased to $34.7 million. This pushed EDUs market cap ranking from 496th to 479th.
  • EDU Chain processed 2.9 million transactions in Q2, a 96.4% QoQ decline from launch-driven highs. Average daily active users fell 70.7% to around 1,600.
  • The total number of deployed contracts grew 19.1% to 26,000, while average daily deployments dropped 80.8% to 46. This indicates a shift toward maintaining and upgrading existing applications or protocol components rather than launching new ones.
  • Open Campus granted Pencil Finance $10 million to advance onchain student lending. The platform aims to direct capital to underserved student populations and offers retail and institutional DeFi participants access to transparent, tokenized lending markets.
  • Open Campus released OC Kickstart, an open-source framework for rapid deployment of Web3-enabled education platforms on EDU Chain. The toolkit integrates core EDU Chain features such as Open Campus ID and Achievements so projects can launch faster without requiring extensive technical resources.

Primer

Open Campus is a Web3 education ecosystem publicly announced in 2023 that seeks to address challenges in global education, like limited access to quality learning, undercompensation of educators, and unreliable credential verification. The platform enables educators to tokenize content for direct monetization, while providing learners with verifiable onchain credentials and access to decentralized student financing. Its ecosystem of education-focused apps connects students and educators, supports skill-building courses, and rewards learning achievements.

At the core of Open Campus infrastructure is EDU Chain, a Layer-3 (L3) blockchain built on the Arbitrum Orbit framework and launched in January 2025. EDU Chain is purpose-built to host education-focused apps, enable onchain education finance (EduFi), and provide the infrastructure for credential issuance and content transactions. Learners can engage with apps on EDU Chain, own their achievements as verifiable credentials, and access globally funded student loans with transparent, onchain terms. Complementing EDU Chain are Publisher NFTs (pNFTs), which allow educators to tokenize and monetize educational materials, and Open Campus ID (OC-ID), a protocol for issuing decentralized identifiers that store an immutable record of a learners academic history across Web2 and Web3 platforms.

The Open Campus DAO governs the protocol through EDU tokenholder voting, with a five-member council elected annually to oversee key decisions. Strategic partners such as Animoca Brands and TinyTap contribute to ecosystem growth, while the Open Campus Accelerator, operated by NewCampus, focuses on onboarding startups and institutions.

For a full primer on Open Campus, refer to our Initiation of Coverage report.

Key Metrics

Performance Analysis

Token Price and Circulating Market Cap

EDU is the native governance and utility token of the Open Campus ecosystem. It supports governance through the Open Campus DAO and serves multiple transactional and functional roles across EDU Chain. EDUs quarter-closing price increased 15.8% from $0.12 in Q1 to $0.13 by the end of Q2 2025. The circulating market capitalization rose in tandem, up by the same percentage from $30.0 million to $34.7 million. EDUs circulating market cap ranking improved modestly over the quarter, moving from 496th to 479th.

EDU Chain Transaction Activity

EDU Chain has processed over 84.4 million transactions since its mainnet was released to the public on Jan. 17, 2025. After a strong first quarter with elevated activity, the number of transactions processed during Q2 dropped 96.4% QoQ to 2.9 million. Average daily transactions fell by the same percentage to about 32,300 from approximately 903,500 in the prior quarter.

EDU Chain User Activity

Average daily active users on EDU Chain declined 70.7% QoQ, falling from approximately 4,600 in Q1 to 1,600 in Q2 2025. Average daily new users dropped more sharply, down 96.5% QoQ from around 2,418 to 86 over the same period. Despite the slowdown in new user growth, the cumulative number of user accounts increased from 179,000 to about 186,800 by quarter-end. Factors that may have contributed to this decline include reduced Yuzu Point rewards, which decreased participation from casual or opportunistic users, along with a post-launch normalization after the heightened activity seen in Q1.

EDU Chain Deployed Contracts

The total number of contracts on EDU Chain increased 19.1% QoQ to 26,000 by the end of Q2 2025. Verified contracts rose from 526 to 625, though the QoQ growth rate slowed to 18.8%, representing a 66.1% decline from the prior quarters pace. In line with this trend, average daily new contract deployments declined 80.8% QoQ from approximately 239 in Q1 to 46 in Q2. This contraction likely reflects reduced developer activity following the initial post-launch period and a shift in focus toward maintaining or upgrading existing apps rather than deploying new contracts.

Qualitative Analysis

Ecosystem Growth

EDU Chain Validator Program Tops 35 Members

The Open Campus Validator Program is a collaborative initiative between Open Campus and College DAO that enables university blockchain clubs to operate Principal Nodes on EDU Chain. By participating, these clubs earn EDU rewards while contributing to the networks decentralization. The program aims to improve blockchain literacy in traditional education by providing hands-on technical experience and promoting the adoption of decentralized technologies.

In Q2 2025, the program surpassed 35 members, with each club actively validating transactions on EDU Chain. These members include established blockchain clubs at institutions like the University of California, Berkeley; New York University; the University of Pennsylvania, Cornell University; and the University of Cambridge, alongside numerous other universities worldwide.

Pencil Finance receives $10 million grant

In Q2 2025, Pencil Finance established a $10 million fund provided by Animoca Brands and Open Campus to underwrite loan capital on the platform. This fund is designed to underwrite principal and interest payments for early investors, safeguarding investments up to this amount and providing additional confidence as the platform scales. The initiative directs capital toward underserved student populations while creating transparent, yield-generating opportunities for both retail and institutional DeFi participants. Lending partners can tokenize student loan packages with parameters such as term length, interest rate, and repayment schedule, listing them as investable pools on the platform. Prospective investors can then explore these pools, assess risk-return profiles through tranche selection, and participate by purchasing fractional shares of bundled loans.

OC Incubator (OC-I) Season Two Concludes

The Open Campus Incubator (OC-I) is a 12-week remote program that supports developers of winning projects from the Hackathon Series in building and scaling apps on EDU Chain. The program offers structured training in product development, marketing, and community engagement, pairing participants with industry mentors and providing access to funding opportunities. In Q2 2025, OC-I completed its second cohort, which included 14 winning projects across DeFi, EduFi, infrastructure, gaming, and learning applications. Over the course of the program, participants refined their products and concluded with a Demo Day showcasing their work to mentors, partners, and potential collaborators.

Additional Ecosystem Developments

Several other projects either launched on EDU Chain during the quarter or advanced the ecosystem through notable milestones:

  • OC Afrika x Base Bridge partnership Base Bridge partnered with Open Campus Afrika to promote onchain education initiatives across the African continent and advance EDU Chains mission to increase accessibility and adoption of onchain learning and financing opportunities.
  • EduHub launch EduHub launched EduAgent on EDU Chain as an AI-powered interface that lets users perform transactions, deploy assets, analyze blockchain data, and access real-time network information through natural language interactions.
  • BAG integrates OC Achievements BAG is an Africa-based talent agency from the fourth OC-X cohort that integrated EDU Chain Achievements to support job simulations, cohort-based upskilling, smart job matching, and role-specific assessments for candidates and employers.
  • Zydii Africa EDU Chain integration Zydii Africa adopted EDU Chain Achievements to strengthen digital workforce training across Africa by delivering upskilling programs for SMEs aimed at reducing turnover and improving job performance.

Development Milestones

Open Campus launches OC Kickstart

In June 2025, Open Campus released OC Kickstart, an open-source application framework designed to enable rapid deployment of Web3-enabled platforms on EDU Chain. The framework supports configurations for online learning marketplaces, gig economy platforms, and assessment systems, and can be deployed within minutes without requiring extensive technical resources.

OC Kickstart includes integrated features such as Open Campus ID for authentication, Open Campus Achievements for credential issuance, an administrative portal, and team management tools. It also offers white-label customization for branding and user interface adjustments while maintaining a standardized backend. The initiative is intended to reduce development time and costs for new projects, while increasing utilization of EDU Chain infrastructure within education and skills-focused applications.

FlowEDU Launch
In Q2 2025, the EDU Chain ecosystem introduced FlowEDU, an automated cross-chain bridge for EDU tokens operating between EDU Chain and BNB Chain. The service addresses common challenges in asset transfers, including multiple transaction steps, network switching, and the need for native gas tokens on several chains.

FlowEDU employs a wallet binding system and backend automation to complete transfers through a single deposit. Once a user sends EDU to a unique FlowEDU address, the system manages gas provisioning, executes the transfer through LayerZero OFT and Arbitrum bridging contracts, and delivers the tokens to the bound wallet on the destination chain. A protocol fee of 0.3% applies to each transaction. The tool streamlines EDU transfers across chains and increases accessibility to EDU Chains ecosystem

EDU Chain partners with thirdweb

In Q2 2025, EDU Chain partnered with thirdweb, a Web3 development platform that provides AI tools, developer infrastructure, and blockchain data services. The integration creates a full-stack development environment tailored to EDU Chain that enables faster application deployment and supports scalable operations.

Key capabilities supported by the partnership include:

  • Account abstraction smart wallets that connect with multiple wallet types and support gasless transactions, batch calls, and session keys.
  • Infrastructure resources such as dedicated RPC and node access, along with the Insight API for fast retrieval of onchain logs, events, and balances.
  • Smart contract deployment tools that allow developers to launch audited, production-ready contracts in seconds and use EDU Chainspecific templates for NFTs, tokens, DAOs, and rewards programs.
  • Data services through thirdwebs indexing and API solutions, providing access to balances, transactions, and contract states without relying on third-party indexers.
  • AI capabilities via Nebula Agents, enabling automated smart contract interactions and onchain data processing directly on EDU Chain.

These resources expand the range of technical tools available to developers building within the EDU Chain ecosystem and reduce development time and operational complexity.

Semester Three Hackathon

The Open Campus Codex Hackathon Series is a multi-event program supporting application development on EDU Chain with a total prize pool of $1 million. In Q2 2025, Season Three concluded with over 9,000 registrations and more than 150 shortlisted projects. It featured six tracks, with AI, DeFi, and Earn designated as priority areas, and Play, DeSci, and Miscellaneous included as additional categories. The $250,000 EDU prize pool was awarded to 36 winning projects that delivered functional prototypes. All winners were invited to join the Open Campus Incubator to further develop their applications.

OCP-15: Reallocation of 20M $EDU for Operational Expenses

In June, the Open Campus DAO approved OCP-15 to reallocate 20 million $EDU from the Ecosystem Fund to the DAOs operational budget. The allocation funds legal, compliance, engineering, governance, and growth functions, and is expected to sustain operations for about twelve months. It aims to preserve EDU Chain infrastructure, manage the treasury, and engage institutional partners while addressing depleted reserves and maintaining essential functions during the networks expansion phase.

Events and Incentive Campaigns

SunsetVibes Side Event

In April, Open Campus co-hosted the Sunset Vibes side event at Web3 Festival with Animoca Brands, Pudgy Penguins, and Capy Friends. The gathering provided an informal setting for industry participants to connect through discussions, music, and giveaways.

Yuzu Spring Bloom Campaign

In June, Open Campus completed the Yuzu: Spring Bloom campaign, the second season of EDU Chains onchain points program. The campaign recorded 82 million EDU staked and $15.52 million in DeFi trading volume, with Yuzu Points distributed for staking, bridging, referrals, and engagement with dApps. All dApps on EDU Chain received baseline allocations, with boosts for Open Campus ID integration and newcomer status, and high performers earned additional midseason drops based on TVL, active wallets, and transaction counts.

Open Campus co-hosts the Monte Carlo WAIB Summit Award

Open Campus partnered with the WAIB Summit in Monaco to co-host the Monte Carlo WAIB Summit Awards. The event recognized innovation and impact across Web3, AI, venture capital, gaming, and decentralized applications.

Closing Summary

Open Campus concluded Q2 2025 with a 15.8% increase in EDUs token price to $0.13 and a parallel rise in circulating market capitalization to $34.7 million. EDU Chain processed 2.9 million transactions, down 96.4% QoQ as activity normalized following launch incentives, while average daily active users fell 70.7% to 1,600. Developer activity slowed, with average daily contract deployments down 80.8%, although total deployed contracts rose 19.1% to 26,000.

Ecosystem growth included the Validator Program surpassing 35 members, a $10 million grant to Pencil Finance to expand onchain student lending, and the completion of OC Incubator Season Two with 14 winning projects across DeFi, EduFi, and learning applications. Key infrastructure releases like OC Kickstart and a partnership with thirdweb expanded development capabilities and streamlined EDU Chain operations. The quarter also featured the Season Three Hackathon, DAO approval of OCP-15 for operational funding, and community engagement through the Yuzu Spring Bloom campaign, event partnerships, and side gatherings at industry conferences.
